node.title: NT records one new local COVID-19 case, hard lockdown ending in Rockhole
node.alt: Northern Territory Chief Minister Michael Gunner speaking at a press conference in Parliament House.
node.description: A teenager from Binjari has tested positive while in quarantine, while negative test results and wastewater has been returned for the community of Rockhole.
node.content:
["The Northern Territory has recorded one\u00a0new local case\u00a0of COVID-19 overnight, Chief Minister Michael Gunner says.", "The Territory's cluster now stands at 52\u00a0cases.", "The new case is a teenager from Binjari who was previously identified as a close contact and was transferred to the Centre for National Resilience\u00a0where he tested positive.", "\"It is unlikely that he was infectious in the community,\" Mr Gunner\u00a0said.", "\"This shows us the hard lockdown is working and that caring for close contacts in quarantine is working.\"", "He said the Bicentennial Road catchment in Katherine East was continuing to return COVID-positive wastewater results, though the strength was weaker.", "\"The wastewater results for this catchment will be critical for tomorrow,\" he said, adding the Martin Place sub-catchment returned positive results and authorities were working to explain that.", "The Rockhole wastewater was negative again and all tests had\u00a0come back negative, Mr Gunner said.", "\"For this reason, Rockhole will transition from a hard lockdown back to an ordinary lockdown today at noon,\" he said.", "\"That means residents in Rockhole are still in lockdown, but can leave home for one of the five reasons.", "\"Under no circumstances are residents of Rockhole permitted to enter the Binjari community.\"", "There were 3,020 tests processed in the Territory in the past 24 hours, including 27 tests done in the housing block where the COVID-positive woman from Binjari visited yesterday.", "There is one new close contact exposure site: the Shell Coles Express on the highway in Katherine on Monday, November 23, between 4:50pm and 5:05pm.", "Mr Gunner urged people to use QR code check-ins at all venues.\u00a0", "\"Not checking in slows down the contact tracers, which slows down our efforts to track and trace the virus, which potentially slows down the transition out of lockdown,\" Mr Gunner said.", "The Salvation Army store in Katherine has been upgraded from a casual contact site to a close contact site.", "Anyone who visited the shop on Saturday, November 13, between 10:30am and 10:50am must get tested and isolate until they return a\u00a0negative test result.", "The number of close contacts now stood\u00a0at 506, Mr Gunner said.", "Of those, 482 have been located and are isolating. These contacts have returned 543 negative results so far.", "\"I know we are all very aware of the huge amount of misinformation being spread online over the past few days,\" Mr Gunner said.", "\"Hello to all the conspiracy theorists overseas watching this. Please get a life.", "\"There are ridiculous, untrue rumours about the ADF's involvement. As we all know, they aren't carrying weapons \u2014 they are carrying fresh food for people.", "\"99.99 per cent of the BS that is flying around on the internet about the Territory is coming from flogs outside the Territory \u2014 mostly America, Canada and the UK, people who have nothing better to do than make up lies about us because their own lives are so small and so sad.\"", "Acting Chief Health Officer Charles Pain said today was \"clearly a positive day\".", "\"We've got one new case in quarantine already, who has been an identified contact,\" he said.", "\"What this demonstrates\u2026 is an enormous effort to contact trace and identify people, and then with our widespread testing we haven't picked up anyone outside that who hasn't already been identified as a contact.\"", "He said two people remained in hospital, with one expecting to be discharged today.", "One of those is a patient in their 70s who is still requiring hospital care, he said.", "More to come.", "", "
What COVID-19 travel insurance doesn't cover you for(Emilia Terzon)
"]
